Senegal is enforcing a Restriction of Mass Gatherings in the regions of Dakar and Thiès from the 6th of January to the 17th of January. This ban includes the following: 
-all processions, parades, gatherings and demonstrations on the public highway;
-all public meetings;
- all private meetings including baptisms, weddings, receptions and religious events;
-all gatherings in places open to the public, in particular hotels, -performance halls, dance halls, bars, cafes, tea rooms, beaches, weekly markets as well as sports grounds and halls.

